flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Make sure canonical platform traffic reaches one honest, active ingress boundary"]
    G2["Answer the basic design question of what the real external traffic boundary is"]
    G3["Establish the correct ingress edge before admission semantics begin"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["Entry is canonical traffic that is actually allowed to behave as traffic"]
    E2["Only behavioural_streams are eligible for ingestion as production traffic"]
    E3["traffic_primitives, behavioural_context, truth_products, audit_evidence, and ops_telemetry are not canonical business traffic"]
    E4["Current traffic policy narrows entry further to s2_event_stream_baseline_6B and s3_event_stream_with_fraud_6B"]
    E5["The correct ingress contract must already be used"]
    E6["Boundary targeting had to be made explicit so a stale internal ALB path could not be silently used instead"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Canonical behavioural stream"]
    R2["Explicit execute-api ingress URL"]
    R3["Stage v1"]
    R4["Route POST /ingest/push"]
    R5["IG Lambda boundary"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Canonical behavioural event payloads"]
    C2["Ingress route contract:<br/>stage v1 + POST /ingest/push"]
    C3["Boundary auth and key material expected by the ingress runtime"]
    C4["Canonical event-envelope rule for anything emitted as behavioural_streams onto a bus"]
    C5["API-key authentication mode"]
    C6["X-IG-Api-Key header"]
    C7["Pinned secret-backed API key contract"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats the external ingress boundary as a first-class system object"]
    L2["The current wired system is not saying: traffic eventually gets in somehow"]
    L3["It is saying: traffic enters through this named, active, externally declared boundary"]
    L4["That makes the wiring legible"]
    L5["It also makes the rest of Group 2 meaningful because admission, disposition, publication, and receipts need one honest live ingress edge first"]
    L6["The current answer is intentionally singular: execute-api ingress URL + stage v1 + POST /ingest/push + IG Lambda handler"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["API name: fraud-platform-dev-full-ig-edge"]
    S2["Ingress URL: https://ehwznd2uw7.execute-api.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/v1"]
    S3["Route: POST /ingest/push"]
    S4["Lambda: fraud-platform-dev-full-ig-handler"]
    S5["Ingress contract remediation aligned runtime to GET /ops/health and POST /ingest/push"]
    S6["Later proving work codified the API Gateway telemetry surface"]
    S7["The obsolete internal ingress path was kept out of the accepted active-boundary story"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["Ambiguity at the front door was treated as a real defect, not a cosmetic nuisance"]
    Y2["Old stage and route drift was corrected to restore the canonical endpoint model"]
    Y3["The launcher was patched to force the correct execute-api target instead of silently resolving a stale internal service URL"]
    Y4["The retained internal ingress stack was treated as a drift hazard because it no longer served the accepted external boundary story"]
    Y5["This shape was produced by deliberately narrowing ingress to one active front door"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The data-engine interface shapes the entry side"]
    X2["Only behavioural_streams are traffic"]
    X3["Non-traffic surfaces must not be treated as business traffic"]
    X4["Traffic emitted at ingestion must conform to the canonical event-envelope contract"]
    X5["Platform authority shapes the boundary side: private-by-default networking with explicit ingress only where required"]
    X6["Secret and config access is governed through pinned handles like /fraud-platform/dev_full/ig/api_key"]
    X7["Every phase uses one active runtime path per phase/run, with fail-closed governance on path selection"]
    X8["So the boundary-access path is shaped both by what traffic is allowed to be and by how the platform is allowed to expose a front door"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path chooses clarity and governance over convenience"]
    T2["It would be easier to let old service URLs linger, let helpers resolve whatever endpoint they find, or tolerate multiple ingress surfaces"]
    T3["The current design rejects that because it makes the boundary story muddy"]
    T4["The cost is more explicitness: explicit execute-api target, explicit route, explicit key contract, explicit exclusion of obsolete ingress surfaces, explicit telemetry on the real front door"]
    T5["That adds ceremony but buys a much cleaner claim: the platform has one real ingress boundary"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, Group 2 loses its clean start"]
    N2["Traffic might still reach something, but the platform could no longer honestly say what its real front door is"]
    N3["It would become unclear whether the old ALB path still counts"]
    N4["It would become unclear whether helpers are proving the active boundary or a stale one"]
    N5["It would become unclear whether boundary evidence and telemetry belong to the right surface"]
    N6["Admission logic, bus publication, and receipts might still exist, but the boundary they supposedly begin from would be hand-wavy"]
    N7["That would directly weaken A because the ingress story would still be ambiguous at the very first hop"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["A request has reached the correct live ingress boundary"]
    O2["The correct route and auth contract were used"]
    O3["The request is now eligible to be processed by the ingress runtime"]
    O4["Owned outcome: the correct active ingress boundary has been reached under the correct contract"]
    O5["This path closes before admission, not after classification"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a specific job for establishing the correct ingress boundary before admission semantics begin"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>the active external front door is singular and explicitly chosen"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the boundary is concretely seated in the execute-api ingress URL, stage v1, POST /ingest/push, and the IG Lambda handler"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>entry traffic is constrained by the engine's traffic taxonomy and canonical event-envelope rule"]
    A5["Quantified closure claim:<br/>one active external front door, one stage, one route, one handler, with the obsolete internal ingress path explicitly excluded"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>the system has one honest external front door instead of an ambiguous ingress story"]
  end

